<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation" id="CITEREFLerner1996">Lerner, Lawrence S. (1996), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://books.google.com/?id=B8K_ym9rS6UC&pg=PA1051"><i>Physics for Scientists and Engineers, Volume 2</i></a>, Jones and Bertlett Publishers, Inc, <a href="International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="Special_BookSources/0-7637-0460-1" title="Special:BookSources/0-7637-0460-1">0-7637-0460-1</a><span class="printonly">, <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://books.google.com/?id=B8K_ym9rS6UC&pg=PA1051">http://books.google.com/?id=B8K_ym9rS6UC&amp;pg=PA1051</a></span></span>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://books.google.be/books?id=B8K_ym9rS6UC&pg=PA1051">Chapter 38 §38.4, p. 1051,1052</a></span></li>
